            <title>[GROOVY-8589] GrapeMain bugfix: should not show error about missing mandatory args when --help or --version is specified</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/GROOVY-8589</link>
                <project id="12318123" key="GROOVY">Groovy</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/GROOVY-8577&quot; title=&quot;Migrate org.codehaus.groovy.tools.GrapeMain.groovy to picocli&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;GROOVY-8577&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;GROOVY-8577&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; introduced a bug: the parser incorrectly complains about missing mandatory options when the user specified --help or --version. For example:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;
java -cp ... org.codehaus.groovy.tools.GrapeMain install --version
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;p&gt;... gives the following output:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;
Missing required parameters: &amp;lt;group&amp;gt;, &amp;lt;module&amp;gt;
Installs a particular grape
Usage: grape install [-hv] &amp;lt;group&amp;gt; &amp;lt;module&amp;gt; [&amp;lt;version&amp;gt;] [&amp;lt;classifier&amp;gt;]

Installs the specified groovy module or maven artifact. If a version is
...
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;</description>
